cs.DB, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CE 

This paper is about a prototype database management system designed specifically for biological data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the use of new access methods and operators for pattern matching on compressed biological data types, which could fall under cs.DL (Digital Libraries) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also mentions the use of content-based authorization for data curation, which could fall under cs.LG (Learning) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
